    .markdown-cheatsheet
      %h4 Headings
      %pre
        :preserve
          # Heading 1
          ## Heading 2
          ### Heading 3
          #### Heading 4
          ##### Heading 5
          ###### Heading 6
      %h4 Text Emphasis
      %pre
        :preserve
          This **will** make text bold.
          And this should _make text_ italic.
          Doing so can ~~strikethrough~~ text. (GFM syntax)
      %h4 Links
      %h5 Normal Links
      %pre
        :preserve
          [Link Text](http://example.com/)
          [Link Text](http://example.com/ "Link Title (optional)")
      %h5 Refrence-Style Links
      %pre
        :preserve
          [Link Text][1]
      %p And then define the reference anywhere in the document:
      %pre
        :preserve
          [1]: http://example.com/ "Link Title (optional)"
      %h4 Images
      %pre
        :preserve
          ![Alt Text](/path/to/image.jpg)
          ![Alt Text](/path/to/image.jpg "Image Title (optional)")
      %p You can also apply reference-style syntax to image, like:
      %pre
        :preserve
          ![Alt Text][2]
          
          [2]: /path/to/image.jpg "Image Title (optional)"
      %h4 Blockquote
      %h5 Basic Quotation
      %pre
        :preserve
          &gt; Quoted
          &gt; Block
          &gt; Text
      %h5 Octopress Quotation Syntax
      %pre
        :preserve
          {% blockquote Author Name %}
          Flying is learning how to throw yourself at the ground and miss.
          {% endblockquote %}
          
          {% blockquote Author Name https://example.com/quotation/source/link %}
          Over the past 24 hours I've been reflecting on my life &amp; I've realized only one thing. I need a medieval battle axe.
          {% endblockquote %}
      %h4 Lists
      %h5 Ordered List
      %pre
        :preserve
          1. List Item #1
          2. List Item #2
          3. List Item #3
      %h5 Unordered List
      %pre
        :preserve
          * List Item #1
          * List Item #2
          * List Item #3
      %h4 Codes
      %h5 Inline Code
      %pre
        :preserve
          Press `Command-Z` to undo.
      %h5 GFM Code Block
      %pre
        :preserve
          ```
          console.log('Hello World!');
          ```
      %h5 GFM Code Block with Language and Title
      %pre
        :preserve
          ``` html welcome.html
          &lt;html&gt;
          ...
          &lt;/html&gt;
          ```
      %h4 Table
      %pre
        :preserve
          | First Header | Second Header | Third Header |
          | ------------ | :-----------: | -----------: |
          | Content      |  center-align |  right-align |
          | Content      |   **Cell**    |         Cell |
          | New section  |     More      |         Data |
